==English==
===Etymology===
From {{Gr.}} '''[[Θεσσαλονίκη]]''' (''Thessaloniki'') (daughter of Philip B' and Nikasipolis of Thessaly, stepsister of Alexander the Great), from '''[[Θεσσαλία]]''' (''Thessalia'') "[[Thessaly]]" + '''[[νίκη]]''' (''nike'') "victory".
===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Thessaloniki'''

#The second-largest city in [[Greece]], capital of the [[Greek Region of Macedonia]].

